- Sapporo too.

249
00:11:34,326 --> 00:11:36,862
I didn't think we'd get this close.

250
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:42,034
I didn't think I'd meet someone like you.

251
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:45,604
I didn't think I'd meet someone
I'd actually want to be with.

252
00:11:45,671 --> 00:11:46,572
Yeah.

253
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:56,315
A mosquito, jeez.

254
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:02,455
Are you lying down? Right now?

255
00:12:03,089 --> 00:12:04,690
Mmm!

256
00:12:05,257 --> 00:12:06,392
Yeah.

257
00:12:09,595 --> 00:12:11,197
- Can I ask you something?
- Mmm.

258
00:12:11,263 --> 00:12:13,866
- In the beginning, in the Green Room?
- Mmm.

259
00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:17,103
- You said you were into William, right?
- Mmm. Mm-hmm.

260
00:12:17,603 --> 00:12:19,672
I don't think you only have one type

261
00:12:20,172 --> 00:12:22,374
when it comes to people you like.

262
00:12:23,642 --> 00:12:24,910
He and I are

263
00:12:26,278 --> 00:12:27,646
pretty different, right?

264
00:12:28,147 --> 00:12:29,381
You mean looks?

265
00:12:29,448 --> 00:12:31,817
- Looks or personality.
- Personality? But…

266
00:12:32,318 --> 00:12:34,220
The things you have in common…

267
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:38,724
- Like, you both have a playful, cute side.
- Playful?

268
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:42,161
Cute personality.
Will has a really cute side to him.

269
00:12:42,795 --> 00:12:46,866
He says random things, he's kinda spacey…
he's just naturally like that.

270
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:47,800
I see.

271
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:52,171
Those, you know,
playful parts are similar.

272
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:54,240
You two are similar in that way.

273
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:57,843
<i>Is he hoping</i>
<i>he'll say they're the same? Or different?</i>

274
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,845
<i>Seems he's waiting for a certain answer.</i>

275
00:12:59,912 --> 00:13:00,746
<i>Yeah.</i>

276
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,616
- Are you okay?
- Mmm?

277
00:13:04,884 --> 00:13:06,585
Just that I'm having fun.

278
00:13:06,652 --> 00:13:07,720
What's fun?

279
00:13:08,754 --> 00:13:12,625
Just thinking how nice it is
being here with you.

280
00:13:30,242 --> 00:13:32,077
- You wanna sleep?
- Mmm.

281
00:13:35,447 --> 00:13:36,615
Nice.

282
00:13:39,852 --> 00:13:40,853
Good night.

283
00:13:42,621 --> 00:13:45,491
What? What's that face? What's that face?

284
00:13:45,558 --> 00:13:49,428
- I can't see your face right now.
- That's why I said good night.

285
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,765
- Good night?
- You can't see my face anyway.

286
00:13:53,265 --> 00:13:55,367
- Then I won't sleep yet.
- Can you tell who I am?

287
00:13:55,434 --> 00:13:58,070
No idea. I have to get closer.

288
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:06,579
- Aah!
- Yes! Yes! Yes!

289
00:14:06,645 --> 00:14:07,813
Yeah!

290
00:14:09,048 --> 00:14:10,549
- You're close.
- Sorry.

291
00:14:11,717 --> 00:14:12,985
You're really close.

292
00:14:13,485 --> 00:14:14,920
- You don't like it?
- What?

293
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:23,762
Mmm.

294
00:14:26,098 --> 00:14:28,100
- Mmm.
- Aah.

295
00:14:31,103 --> 00:14:32,304
Come here.

296
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:55,628
I'll stay with you.

297
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,098
I'm already right here with you.

298
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:06,138
- That was amazing, right from the start!
- That's wonderful!

299
00:15:06,205 --> 00:15:08,874
We were literally like this,
glued to the screen!

300
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:11,944
- They got so close so fast.
- Yeah.

301
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,412
That was so good.

302
00:15:13,479 --> 00:15:16,649
When those two got in the bed, like,
"What's gonna happen?"

303
00:15:16,715 --> 00:15:18,284
And he said "Good night!"

304
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:20,185
That "Good night" was--

305
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:22,955
That really means, "Are we
really stopping here?" Right?

306
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:25,324
- That was so good!
- You liked that?

307
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:27,927
I could hear that a hundred
times in my life!

308
00:15:27,993 --> 00:15:30,396
That's why he's straight out
of a shojo manga.

309
00:15:30,462 --> 00:15:33,799
He wants to be pulled in, but can't
say it, so he says "good night" instead.

310
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:36,435
That hand gesture was like
a signal of "Pull me in."

311
00:15:36,502 --> 00:15:40,406
He loves sending all those little signals
and then getting pulled in tight.

312
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:41,440
- No?
- I get that.

313
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:43,342
It cannot be just having fun.

314
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:46,145
He's like, "Tell me more
about how you feel about me."

315
00:15:46,211 --> 00:15:47,947
- Yeah.
- He's a princess.

316
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:49,148
Yeah.

317
00:15:49,214 --> 00:15:51,784
But he keeps talking about
how much he admires Taeheon.

318
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:52,918
Yeah.

319
00:15:52,985 --> 00:15:56,622
It probably makes him
unsure how to respond.

320
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:59,858
Even during the story about
the first coffee truck shift being rough,

321
00:15:59,925 --> 00:16:02,094
he listens with
that unreadable expression.

322
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:05,331
When someone says,
"I liked you from the last season."

323
00:16:05,397 --> 00:16:08,701
I'm sure he wonders if
he likes him on the TV show

324
00:16:08,767 --> 00:16:11,403
or he likes the real him off-screen.

325
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:13,172
He probably can't tell.

326
00:16:13,672 --> 00:16:15,975
So he wants to hear
something more specific.

327
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:20,746
Whether he likes the real him
or just admires him as a reality TV star.

328
00:16:24,016 --> 00:16:25,317
Let's eat.

329
00:16:26,852 --> 00:16:28,487
From before coming here

330
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:31,657
to today, has something changed?

331
00:16:32,858 --> 00:16:34,159
It has, um…

332
00:16:36,228 --> 00:16:39,231
A lot has changed, right?

333
00:16:39,898 --> 00:16:42,201
- Something has.
- Something?

334
00:16:42,801 --> 00:16:46,105
Yeah, we've gotten… closer.

335
00:16:49,975 --> 00:16:52,911
When we walked into that place,

336
00:16:52,978 --> 00:16:55,681
I already couldn't hold it in.

337
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:59,118
And once we got into bed,
of course I wanted to sleep next to him.

338
00:16:59,918 --> 00:17:02,054
I think I was the one
who got closer to him.

339
00:17:02,121 --> 00:17:02,988
But

340
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,592
he kissed me first.

341
00:17:06,658 --> 00:17:08,260
- Oh my!
- It was sudden.

342
00:17:09,895 --> 00:17:11,930
- Like, bam.
- <i>Bam. He came in strong.</i>

343
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:12,998
<i>He did.</i>

344
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:16,735
It felt like something just snapped,

345
00:17:17,636 --> 00:17:19,838
and everything started,

346
00:17:20,739 --> 00:17:21,840
all at once.

347
00:17:22,341 --> 00:17:24,343
We didn't go all the way.

348
00:17:26,145 --> 00:17:27,079
Mmm.

349
00:17:28,747 --> 00:17:29,982
It was good.

350
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,885
I honestly wanted to in the morning, too.

351
00:17:36,021 --> 00:17:38,490
Has something changed? Anything?

352
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:42,895
Being alone together
lets us talk about a lot of things.

353
00:17:42,961 --> 00:17:45,497
And there were things I realized,

354
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:47,366
like what kind of person you are.

355
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,068
- You did? Really?
- Yeah.

356
00:17:50,035 --> 00:17:51,336
I'm glad.

357
00:18:03,449 --> 00:18:05,884
- Ah, man, -that was fun.
- Yeah.

358
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:10,255
- Oh!
- Oh.

359
00:18:10,322 --> 00:18:12,858
- Welcome back!
- We're home.

360
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:15,260
- Lunch is ready.
- Really?

361
00:18:15,994 --> 00:18:17,596
Yeah, it's lunchtime.

362
00:18:18,564 --> 00:18:20,099
Is everyone doing well?

363
00:18:20,165 --> 00:18:22,801
- We're good!
- That's a lot of soba.

364
00:18:25,337 --> 00:18:27,372
- Did you have fun?
- It was great!

365
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:32,044
The place was amazing. It was so good,
I almost feel bad for you guys.

366
00:18:32,111 --> 00:18:34,546
- Really?
- Really. It was incredible, right?

367
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:36,782
- In a wide open field.
- Wow.

368
00:18:36,849 --> 00:18:39,384
- Thank you guys so much.
- That's great.

369
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:41,286
I'm glad. Mmm.

370
00:18:46,658 --> 00:18:49,461
"Hiroya will be taking
today's shift at the coffee truck."

371
00:18:49,528 --> 00:18:51,630
- <i>Here we go!</i>
- <i>So he's got a chance.</i>

372
00:18:51,697 --> 00:18:53,298
- <i>Of course.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

373
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:04,610
<i>Oh! He went that way!</i>

374
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:06,044
- <i>Here?</i>
- Finally!

375
00:19:06,111 --> 00:19:09,248
I thought I'd like to team up
with Jobu for the first time.

376
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,483
I'm excited. Let's go.

377
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:13,352
- Have fun.
- We're off!

378
00:19:15,287 --> 00:19:17,156
Finally.

379
00:19:17,222 --> 00:19:19,892
- Isn't that kind of… very Hiroya?
- Yeah, yeah.

380
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:22,928
- Before going to the person he wants--
- He used to do that a lot early on.

381
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:25,230
- We saw those moments all the time.
- Exactly, early Hiroya!

382
00:19:31,236 --> 00:19:34,840
Thanks for waiting.
One small drip coffee. Thank you.

383
00:19:34,907 --> 00:19:37,676
- Thank you, thanks for waiting.
- Hope to see you again.

384
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:40,679
That end rush was wild.

385
00:19:40,746 --> 00:19:42,214
Wow, that's amazing.

386
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:43,615
TODAY'S SALES:
6,650 YEN

387
00:19:44,983 --> 00:19:46,018
All right.

388
00:19:47,419 --> 00:19:48,287
Aah!

389
00:19:49,288 --> 00:19:51,056
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

390
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:57,062
I've been wanting to try ramen
like this. It's pretty rich. Wow!

391
00:20:00,632 --> 00:20:02,334
Mmm. This is good!

392
00:20:05,737 --> 00:20:07,039
This is crazy good.

393
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:11,210
Crazy good? Is that Hokkaido slang?

394
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:14,246
How are you going to spend this last week?

395
00:20:14,313 --> 00:20:16,114
Yeah, I guess

396
00:20:17,349 --> 00:20:19,751
I'll probably express what I'm feeling.

397
00:20:19,818 --> 00:20:23,222
So there's stuff you haven't said?
You went to Sapporo.

398
00:20:23,288 --> 00:20:24,723
I haven't said it at all.

399
00:20:24,790 --> 00:20:26,325
- Oh, really?
- I haven't said it.

400
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:28,393
Maybe it's kind of obvious in my behavior.

401
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:29,895
Yeah, it's obvious.

402
00:20:29,962 --> 00:20:32,297
- But not in words.
- Come on, literally everyone can tell.

403
00:20:32,364 --> 00:20:34,499
I haven't… I haven't said it.

404
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:37,836
Oh, really? You're not the type to say it?

405
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:40,372
I haven't said it yet.
What am I supposed to say?

406
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:42,241
Like, "I like you."

407
00:20:42,307 --> 00:20:44,943
I haven't. I didn't say it to Will either.

408
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:48,046
But I can't say it unless it's, like,

409
00:20:48,113 --> 00:20:51,483
getting really serious,
or "I want to be with you."

410
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:54,086
So I haven't said it yet.

411
00:20:54,152 --> 00:20:57,623
- That's interesting.
- But this time, I might say it.

412
00:20:57,689 --> 00:21:00,325
- I think that's good.
- I might be able to.

413
00:21:00,392 --> 00:21:03,829
- You should.
- It feels stronger than last time.

414
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:06,231
My feelings. Mmm.

415
00:21:06,865 --> 00:21:08,500
But what about you, Hiroya?

416
00:21:09,368 --> 00:21:11,903
I mean, with you here, it's awkward,

417
00:21:12,404 --> 00:21:15,073
but yeah, I have feelings for Taeheon.

418
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:16,208
But,

419
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:19,044
like, in the first half,

420
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:22,648
you can fall in love,
but you can't have a relationship alone.

421
00:21:22,714 --> 00:21:23,949
Yeah, true.

422
00:21:24,016 --> 00:21:27,486
It depends on
what the other person thinks.

423
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:30,856
Before entering the Green Room,

424
00:21:32,024 --> 00:21:33,825
I couldn't express myself.

425
00:21:33,892 --> 00:21:36,595
- But I've been working hard on that.
- Mmm.

426
00:21:37,663 --> 00:21:40,198
If I'm into someone, I say it.
That's what I decided.

427
00:21:40,265 --> 00:21:42,968
- Mmm.
- So I'm doing that with Taeheon too.

428
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:47,406
I think I'll just keep expressing
how I feel, all the way through.

429
00:21:47,906 --> 00:21:51,943
- I guess that's what I'm doing.
- I see.

430
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:54,479
<i>He probably wanted</i>
<i>to say that properly to Jobu.</i>

431
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:55,747
<i>Probably.</i>

432
00:21:58,050 --> 00:21:59,384
It's pouring.

433
00:22:00,052 --> 00:22:01,820
Hey, are you any good at Othello?

434
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:02,854
I'm not good.

435
00:22:03,455 --> 00:22:04,790
What do you want if you win?

436
00:22:05,290 --> 00:22:07,559
- What do you want if you lose?
- If I lose…

437
00:22:08,060 --> 00:22:10,362
- A wish.
- A wish?

438
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:12,297
- If you win…
- If I win.

439
00:22:12,364 --> 00:22:15,634
I'll grant your wish.

440
00:22:15,701 --> 00:22:17,269
You will? Really?

441
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:20,105
Yeah. And I'm gonna win. For sure.

442
00:22:20,872 --> 00:22:21,940
Okay.

443
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,509
First or second? Rock, paper, scissors.

444
00:22:24,576 --> 00:22:26,311
Tie. Go. Go.

445
00:22:26,378 --> 00:22:28,213
- Which do you want?
- I won.

446
00:22:28,714 --> 00:22:30,082
White or black?

447
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:32,050
- Black.
- Black? Okay.

448
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:34,019
Wait, wait.

449
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:36,488
- I'm totally gonna win.
- Slow down.

450
00:22:36,988 --> 00:22:38,056
Wait a sec.

451
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:40,792
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

452
00:22:43,562 --> 00:22:44,996
Is this spot shaved?

453
00:22:45,063 --> 00:22:46,365
- Hmm?
- It's not growing?

454
00:22:46,431 --> 00:22:48,133
- Huh?
- There's nothing here.

455
00:22:49,901 --> 00:22:50,902
Hmm.

456
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:53,004
Yeah… It got shaved.

457
00:22:53,071 --> 00:22:54,106
Here!

458
00:22:54,606 --> 00:22:56,508
Yes, yes, yes, yes,
yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

459
00:23:01,747 --> 00:23:02,614
Huh?

460
00:23:03,648 --> 00:23:05,384
- Huh?
- What's your strategy?

461
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:07,586
- Strategy?
- Are you focused?

462
00:23:07,652 --> 00:23:08,854
I am!

463
00:23:09,588 --> 00:23:11,656
Don't underestimate me.

464
00:23:12,991 --> 00:23:14,826
- <i>Jobu can't focus.</i>
- <i>Yeah.</i>

465
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:17,062
- <i>It's cute.</i>
- <i>He just wants to flirt.</i>

466
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:19,097
I really wanna win.

467
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:23,468
Aww, I lost.

468
00:23:23,535 --> 00:23:25,670
Yeah, I definitely lost.

469
00:23:26,505 --> 00:23:28,774
I was on the harder side, wasn't I?

470
00:23:29,274 --> 00:23:31,410
You said you'd grant any wish.

471
00:23:31,476 --> 00:23:33,812
Oh, so that means I'm the one
taking the penalty then, right?

472
00:23:33,879 --> 00:23:34,813
No, no, no.

473
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:36,915
All right, what should my wish be?

474
00:23:37,983 --> 00:23:40,852
- Make it spicy.
- Maybe I'll make it really spicy.

475
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:42,554
Something you can't even handle.

476
00:23:42,621 --> 00:23:44,556
Is there even something I can't handle?

477
00:23:45,557 --> 00:23:47,159
Well…

478
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:51,696
I'm actually practicing cooking right now.

479
00:23:52,964 --> 00:23:54,666
So I want you

480
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:58,737
to eat my homemade food.

481
00:24:01,506 --> 00:24:03,875
- That's my wish.
- Okay.

482
00:24:04,376 --> 00:24:06,578
- But just the two of us.
- Got it.

483
00:24:07,879 --> 00:24:10,081
- Sometime after tomorrow.
- Okay.

484
00:24:10,148 --> 00:24:12,417
That's all you want?

485
00:24:12,484 --> 00:24:15,020
That's such a cute wish.

486
00:24:16,588 --> 00:24:17,889
We're out of bananas.

487
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:19,057
We ran out?

488
00:24:19,758 --> 00:24:23,161
- I ate the last one this morning.
- How dare you?

489
00:24:23,228 --> 00:24:25,897
That's why I'm not puffy anymore.

490
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,633
How could you? I was looking for one.

491
00:24:29,301 --> 00:24:30,502
I'll buy more later.

492
00:24:32,003 --> 00:24:33,605
- Ryuki!
- Welcome back.

493
00:24:33,672 --> 00:24:36,908
- You look fresh!
- Ah, you cut your hair!

494
00:24:36,975 --> 00:24:39,211
- Ryu-ryu!
- Welcome back.

495
00:24:39,611 --> 00:24:41,413
You look… more mature?

496
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,949
- It's the haircut.
- He's smiling so much.

497
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:45,550
It felt like forever!

498
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:47,519
- It's been a week.
- Finally got to see you.

499
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:48,920
Huh? Are we missing one?

500
00:24:48,987 --> 00:24:50,422
Huwei's in Thailand right now.

501
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:51,823
Oh, in Thailand?

502
00:24:52,624 --> 00:24:53,492
Thailand? Yeah?

503
00:24:54,125 --> 00:24:56,361
- A souvenir?
- Should we ask?

504
00:24:56,862 --> 00:24:57,729
Ahem.

505
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:00,332
Ahem. Hmm, hmm, hmm.

506
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:05,704
I forgot to get souvenirs.

507
00:25:06,238 --> 00:25:09,407
- Having Ryuki back is the real souvenir.
- Yeah, that was the souvenir.

508
00:25:10,308 --> 00:25:11,510
Sorry, guys.

509
00:25:18,917 --> 00:25:20,752
- Hu-hu!
- What! You're back!

510
00:25:20,819 --> 00:25:23,421
- Welcome back… Wait, no. I'm home!
- Not welcome back.

511
00:25:23,488 --> 00:25:25,123
Why are you saying welcome back?

512
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:27,659
- I missed you guys!
- We finally have everyone.

513
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:29,794
Did that elephant T-shirt
come in that color?

514
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,696
- It's a different color.
- Yeah.

515
00:25:31,763 --> 00:25:34,499
I'm just so happy. Happy.

516
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,102
- I missed you guys.
- We missed you too.

517
00:25:37,168 --> 00:25:38,470
- Welcome back!
- I'm home!

518
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:40,372
- You surprised me.
- I've been waiting.

519
00:25:40,438 --> 00:25:41,740
Waiting for a long time.

520
00:25:42,307 --> 00:25:44,643
<i>They kept missing each other,</i>
<i>so it's been a while.</i>

521
00:25:44,709 --> 00:25:47,212
- Ryuki also just got back.
- Really?

522
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:48,480
Oh, right. I brought souvenirs.

523
00:25:48,547 --> 00:25:51,149
- No way, you didn't have to!
- You didn't need to.

524
00:25:51,216 --> 00:25:53,518
- You didn't have to!
- You don't have to.

525
00:25:53,585 --> 00:25:56,588
You weren't even looking at Huwei.
You were looking at me the whole time.

526
00:25:56,655 --> 00:25:59,257
I kind of wanted Ryuki
to try a little bite.

527
00:25:59,324 --> 00:26:01,793
- Oh?
- Durian.

528
00:26:01,860 --> 00:26:04,329
- Ugh.
- Freeze-dried durian.

529
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:05,764
What? I've never had durian.

530
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:08,233
- Why me?
- You said you hated it.

531
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:11,002
- Why get that for me?
- You bought something he hates!

532
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:12,370
Bomi, you're jealous!

533
00:26:12,437 --> 00:26:14,706
- It's the king of fruits!
- What?

534
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:17,275
Oh. Wait…

535
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,446
This souvenir… Sorry.
Hold on, I might not handle this.

536
00:26:21,513 --> 00:26:23,248
- Have some. Have some.
- No, I'm okay.

537
00:26:23,315 --> 00:26:24,649
- I'm good.
- Try it!

538
00:26:24,716 --> 00:26:26,718
- Give it a try!
- I'll see your reaction first.

539
00:26:26,785 --> 00:26:28,753
- Wait.
- It's a souvenir for you.

540
00:26:28,820 --> 00:26:30,355
A souvenir? Thanks.

541
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:32,157
The souvenir that you didn't bring.

542
00:26:32,657 --> 00:26:33,658
One bite.

543
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,467
I can't bite it.

544
00:26:42,534 --> 00:26:45,804
- What do you mean?
- I can't… I can't bite this.

545
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:47,439
- You try it once.
- You can't bite?

546
00:26:47,505 --> 00:26:49,908
- It's too smelly?
- You don't want to?

547
00:26:49,975 --> 00:26:51,242
Try it once.

548
00:26:55,747 --> 00:26:57,215
Did you just age ten years?2

549
00:26:57,782 --> 00:26:59,818
- Oh.
- Aah… Ugh.

550
00:27:00,318 --> 00:27:01,886
What flavor is this?

551
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:03,288
It's durian.

552
00:27:03,355 --> 00:27:04,889
Huh? Weird.

553
00:27:06,324 --> 00:27:07,359
But it's good.

554
00:27:07,425 --> 00:27:09,427
Yeah, the durian
just explodes in your mouth.

555
00:27:09,494 --> 00:27:12,297
- It's normal durian.
- Regular durian.

556
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:15,367
Over there, they're the type
who can eat durian like it's nothing.

557
00:27:16,534 --> 00:27:18,970
Oh, here it comes.

558
00:27:23,108 --> 00:27:25,110
I'll announce today's shift.

559
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:28,913
"Ryuki will be the one
taking today's shift."

560
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,048
Ooh!

561
00:27:30,115 --> 00:27:32,917
"Ryuki, please choose
one person you want to work with."

562
00:27:41,559 --> 00:27:45,296
- <i>Taeheon!</i>
- <i>Teho's really popular lately.</i>

563
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:49,567
- Let's do it.
- Let's go.

564
00:27:49,634 --> 00:27:52,437
- Have a good shift. Good luck.
- Have fun.

565
00:27:53,071 --> 00:27:54,539
- Okay, then.
- See you.

566
00:27:56,474 --> 00:27:58,810
<i>Maybe he wants</i>
<i>a little life guidance from him.</i>

567
00:27:58,877 --> 00:27:59,944
<i>Could be that too.</i>

568
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:02,380
- <i>Oh! I'm happy for them.</i>
- <i>Aah!</i>

569
00:28:02,447 --> 00:28:04,182
- <i>That's great!</i>
- Aah!

570
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:07,419
So…

571
00:28:08,153 --> 00:28:09,721
what did you do last week?

572
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:11,656
We actually did a lot.

573
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:14,025
First, we went to a farm.

574
00:28:14,793 --> 00:28:17,328
- Cows.
- Yeah, we fed the cows.

575
00:28:17,395 --> 00:28:19,364
It was like a date activity.

576
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:22,067
- Jobu likes Taeheon, right?
- Mm-hmm.

577
00:28:22,133 --> 00:28:26,504
- Hiroya wanted to go with Taeheon too.
- Mmm, mmm.

578
00:28:26,571 --> 00:28:29,340
- Then Jobu got picked.
- Mmm.

579
00:28:29,908 --> 00:28:31,876
- And those two went on a sleepover date.
- Mmm.

580
00:28:31,943 --> 00:28:34,546
We went to the farm, fed the cows.

581
00:28:35,180 --> 00:28:37,749
- And went to the volcano café.
- That sounds so fun.

582
00:28:38,249 --> 00:28:40,151
That's why I wanted to go with you.

583
00:28:40,218 --> 00:28:42,153
- I wanted to go too.
- Together.

584
00:28:43,188 --> 00:28:46,024
This switching from portrait
to landscape is cute.

585
00:28:46,524 --> 00:28:47,659
Very cute.

586
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:50,929
Hmm…

587
00:28:50,995 --> 00:28:52,530
I missed you.

588
00:28:53,031 --> 00:28:54,265
Hmm?

589
00:28:54,332 --> 00:28:55,166
- Nothing.
- Huh?

590
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:57,068
<i>He just said it so smoothly.</i>

591
00:28:57,135 --> 00:28:58,403
I seriously missed you.

592
00:29:02,774 --> 00:29:04,542
- A lot.
- Huh?

593
00:29:04,609 --> 00:29:05,944
I missed you a lot.

594
00:29:06,778 --> 00:29:08,580
- I missed you too.
- Mmm.

595
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:13,151
Huwei is back!

596
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:16,588
I'm really happy.

597
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:19,624
<i>But about the souvenir…</i>

598
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:21,493
<i>I had mixed feelings.</i>

599
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:24,963
I was like, "Was it for Ryuki?"

600
00:29:25,964 --> 00:29:27,232
If you like someone,

601
00:29:27,732 --> 00:29:29,434
you think about the other person.

602
00:29:29,501 --> 00:29:31,469
Like, "He might like this."

603
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:35,907
Even small thoughtful things
make you happy.

604
00:29:36,407 --> 00:29:37,308
Yeah.

605
00:29:37,909 --> 00:29:41,312
I want to know how much
Huwei actually likes me.

606
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:44,115
- <i>You end up wanting that.</i>
- <i>Sure.</i>

607
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:46,584
Nice weather.

608
00:29:46,651 --> 00:29:48,553
Yeah, it's really good.

609
00:29:49,687 --> 00:29:50,789
KUMAYAKI

610
00:29:50,855 --> 00:29:51,823
Hello.

611
00:29:51,890 --> 00:29:55,293
- Would you like some coffee?
- If you'd like-- Oh, so cute!

612
00:29:55,860 --> 00:29:56,928
Hello.

613
00:29:56,995 --> 00:29:58,830
- You okay?
- Want some coffee?

614
00:29:58,897 --> 00:30:00,198
Are you guys from Korea?

615
00:30:00,265 --> 00:30:01,466
Yes, I'm from Korea.

616
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:03,535
- I'm from Osaka.
- Oh, I see.

617
00:30:04,035 --> 00:30:05,136
Ah, sorry.

618
00:30:06,237 --> 00:30:07,405
- Cute.
- Cute!

619
00:30:08,907 --> 00:30:11,009
- Where did you put that thing?
- Found it.

620
00:30:11,643 --> 00:30:12,610
All good.

621
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:18,249
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

622
00:30:18,316 --> 00:30:19,551
So cute!

623
00:30:21,519 --> 00:30:23,421
Thank you so much.

624
00:30:23,488 --> 00:30:24,556
So cute!

625
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:28,426
Like Kazuyuki, when I get a boyfriend,

626
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,829
I want to have a dog together.

627
00:30:32,630 --> 00:30:34,532
- But it's sad when they're gone.
- Huh?

628
00:30:34,599 --> 00:30:36,668
Wouldn't you be sad when they're gone?

629
00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:38,603
What do you mean? Kazu?

630
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:40,138
No. The dog.

631
00:30:40,205 --> 00:30:43,007
- The dog!
- Doesn't mean I wouldn't miss Kazuyuki.

632
00:30:45,810 --> 00:30:47,445
I think we are above 5,000.

633
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:49,747
TODAY'S SALES:
6,400 YEN

634
00:30:49,814 --> 00:30:51,683
Well, we did great today.

635
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:54,018
- Shall we sit here?
- Yeah.

636
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:55,220
<i>The snow is melting.</i>

637
00:30:55,286 --> 00:30:57,689
- <i>The season is changing.</i>
- <i>And the sunlight.</i>

638
00:30:58,189 --> 00:31:00,358
- I've been wanting to ask.
- Ask what?

639
00:31:00,425 --> 00:31:03,027
- About… coming out.
- Ah.

640
00:31:04,629 --> 00:31:08,600
Your situation, coming out
after leaving here,

641
00:31:09,234 --> 00:31:11,970
felt similar to mine, you know.

642
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:15,573
So I want to know

643
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:17,942
how your feelings changed
before you said it.

644
00:31:18,009 --> 00:31:19,177
Mmm…

645
00:31:20,345 --> 00:31:23,248
Well… I struggled a lot.

646
00:31:24,048 --> 00:31:27,919
I also thought about giving up many times.

647
00:31:27,986 --> 00:31:29,687
Mmm. Yeah.

648
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:33,658
I thought about many things.

649
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:39,831
But being in a place like the Green Room,
I'm so glad I met everyone.

650
00:31:39,898 --> 00:31:44,469
First, we became friends,
and we built a real bond.

651
00:31:44,969 --> 00:31:47,272
And I started realizing that

652
00:31:48,172 --> 00:31:50,141
I'm not alone, you know?

653
00:31:51,142 --> 00:31:52,710
Even the worst case scenario,

654
00:31:52,777 --> 00:31:54,946
even if my parents,

655
00:31:55,446 --> 00:31:57,815
uh, didn't fully accept me,

656
00:31:58,983 --> 00:32:02,987
if I think of the Green Room boys
as my family,

657
00:32:04,322 --> 00:32:06,457
it didn't feel as scary anymore.

658
00:32:09,127 --> 00:32:11,863
That's how I felt, I guess. Um…

659
00:32:13,164 --> 00:32:16,935
At first, of course,
being on this show meant

660
00:32:17,001 --> 00:32:20,371
being in a situation
where I had to come out.

661
00:32:21,572 --> 00:32:24,976
I mean… I put myself in that place.

662
00:32:26,611 --> 00:32:28,947
But as I spent time with everyone,

663
00:32:29,580 --> 00:32:33,484
my thoughts slowly changed, day by day.

664
00:32:34,819 --> 00:32:37,088
I didn't want to say it unwillingly.

665
00:32:37,588 --> 00:32:38,556
Uh…

666
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:43,661
I wanted to talk and express it properly,
you know?

667
00:32:43,728 --> 00:32:45,129
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

668
00:32:48,499 --> 00:32:50,101
Mmm.

669
00:32:50,168 --> 00:32:53,771
There are a lot of emotions here.

670
00:32:53,838 --> 00:32:56,274
And Taeheon is giving advice

671
00:32:56,341 --> 00:33:00,144
about what comes after this whole
experience of being on this show.

672
00:33:00,211 --> 00:33:02,880
I think Ryuki came here with
the intention, or at least the resolve,

673
00:33:02,947 --> 00:33:05,049
to eventually talk to his dad about this.

674
00:33:05,116 --> 00:33:09,153
But it still feels like he hasn't
fully settled into that decision yet.

675
00:33:09,220 --> 00:33:11,956
Which is completely understandable,
because it's not easy at all.

676
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:15,293
I think that's why he wanted
to ask Taeheon about a lot of things.

677
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:18,096
Right. Taeheon's advice isn't
just pretty words.

678
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:20,365
- It comes from real experience.
- Exactly.

679
00:33:20,431 --> 00:33:22,166
It's the hardest thing, right?

680
00:33:22,233 --> 00:33:24,836
To speak with real weight
and real credibility.

681
00:33:24,902 --> 00:33:28,039
Being able to do that,
that's his emotional maturity.

682
00:33:28,106 --> 00:33:29,407
Absolutely.

683
00:33:29,907 --> 00:33:32,310
Taeheon's different
than when he's in princess mode!

684
00:33:32,377 --> 00:33:35,880
- The contrast is huge.
- In love, he becomes a different person.

685
00:33:35,947 --> 00:33:38,483
- So that's what love does.
- People are like that.

686
00:33:39,484 --> 00:33:44,055
And to be fair, Jobu still hasn't
actually said "I like you."

687
00:33:44,122 --> 00:33:47,658
Yeah. Even though he said things
equal to "I like you."

688
00:33:47,725 --> 00:33:50,361
Yeah. Maybe the reason
Taeheon was insisting,

689
00:33:50,428 --> 00:33:52,030
"Say something else, say something more,"

690
00:33:52,096 --> 00:33:55,099
is because
Jobu never actually said the word.

691
00:33:55,166 --> 00:33:57,368
- I see.
- That's what I got from it.

692
00:33:57,902 --> 00:34:01,272
And then Huwei came back
and Ryuki came back.

693
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:02,507
That's good.

694
00:34:03,007 --> 00:34:07,245
That timing, when Hu said,
"I missed you." Wasn't that perfect?

695
00:34:07,311 --> 00:34:08,980
So cute. It's the first time

696
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:11,482
they looked at something
on a phone together without drama.

697
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:13,217
- In this series!
- True!

698
00:34:13,284 --> 00:34:14,986
Exactly.

699
00:34:27,965 --> 00:34:30,068
- Oh.
- Good morning.

700
00:34:30,134 --> 00:34:32,370
Ah. You okay, Jobu?

701
00:34:32,437 --> 00:34:33,771
- I'm good.
- You good?

702
00:34:33,838 --> 00:34:35,440
- Yeah.
- Good, good.

703
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:38,576
I'm planning to make dinner

704
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:41,612
for Taeheon, but not everyone.

705
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:42,914
Just for him. For him?

706
00:34:42,980 --> 00:34:46,284
- Nice, go for it.
- I promised him I'd cook.

707
00:34:46,350 --> 00:34:48,186
- With Taeheon?
- Yeah.

708
00:34:48,252 --> 00:34:51,355
I'll cook for him for the first time.

709
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:52,924
I bought the ingredients.

710
00:34:52,990 --> 00:34:54,759
So what do we do about our dinner?

711
00:34:54,826 --> 00:34:58,396
Just cook for yourselves.
Not for me and Taeheon.

712
00:34:58,463 --> 00:34:59,964
You aren't eating today's meal?

713
00:35:00,031 --> 00:35:01,099
- Mmm.
- Okay.

714
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,269
- <i>What will he make?</i>
- <i>Wonder what it is.</i>

715
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:17,148
- You using this stove?
- No.

716
00:35:17,215 --> 00:35:19,917
- Okay.
- Actually… no. I'm not using it.

717
00:35:19,984 --> 00:35:21,219
Just the oven.

718
00:35:23,888 --> 00:35:25,456
<i>Watching Jobu</i>

719
00:35:26,390 --> 00:35:29,961
<i>take his time preparing</i>
<i>the surprise meal for Taeheon today</i>…

720
00:35:30,528 --> 00:35:33,064
Um, I guess, I felt like

721
00:35:34,098 --> 00:35:35,800
our pace is just different.

722
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,835
Of course Taeheon gives him

723
00:35:38,336 --> 00:35:41,339
a different kind of response
than he gives me.

724
00:35:42,607 --> 00:35:46,110
But I thought… "Wow, Jobu is amazing."

725
00:35:49,914 --> 00:35:51,883
- <i>That's nice. Romantic.</i>
- <i>Lovely.</i>

726
00:35:51,949 --> 00:35:54,352
<i>You're eating here? Cute!</i>

727
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:02,727
- Welcome back.
- I'm back.

728
00:36:03,361 --> 00:36:04,462
Here they are.

729
00:36:04,962 --> 00:36:06,397
Let's eat outside tonight.

730
00:36:06,464 --> 00:36:10,101
- Huh? Outside?
- Only us. I made dinner!

731
00:36:10,735 --> 00:36:13,171
- Let's eat, just the two of us.
- Two of us?

732
00:36:13,237 --> 00:36:15,940
- Outside?
- Outside. Over there. Right there.

733
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:24,615
Which side do you want? This one?

734
00:36:24,682 --> 00:36:26,150
- This side.
- Okay.

735
00:36:26,651 --> 00:36:28,186
I made it!

736
00:36:28,686 --> 00:36:30,087
What did you make?

737
00:36:30,154 --> 00:36:32,323
- Lasagna?
- I made lasagna!

738
00:36:32,390 --> 00:36:35,026
- Thank you.
- Ah, lasagna!

739
00:36:35,092 --> 00:36:37,528
- Not sure if it turned out right.
- You worked hard.

740
00:36:37,628 --> 00:36:38,696
Cheers.

741
00:36:38,763 --> 00:36:40,498
- Good job.
- Cheers.

742
00:36:44,402 --> 00:36:47,271
- Mmm. Here we go.
- Mmm.

743
00:36:50,942 --> 00:36:52,076
Is it hot?

744
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,178
Maybe.

745
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:56,447
I hope it's cooked all the way.

746
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:01,052
Is it cooked? Not cold inside?

747
00:37:01,485 --> 00:37:04,155
- It tastes good.
- Good? I'm glad it's good.

748
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:06,591
- Glad to hear it.
- It's really good.

749
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:09,694
I kept worrying,
messed up a few times making it.

750
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,495
Doesn't this take a long time?

751
00:37:11,996 --> 00:37:13,598
About an hour and a half.

752
00:37:13,664 --> 00:37:15,833
- An hour and a half?
- Well, maybe an hour.

753
00:37:16,767 --> 00:37:19,670
Thanks. You really put effort into it.

754
00:37:19,737 --> 00:37:21,105
I wanted to try making it.

755
00:37:23,741 --> 00:37:26,310
Whoa! Deer. A parent and a baby.

756
00:37:26,377 --> 00:37:28,479
- So cute. Really cute.
- They noticed us.

757
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:33,751
It's nice coming home from work
and having dinner made.

758
00:37:33,818 --> 00:37:37,288
- Mmm.
- Especially when it's just for me.

759
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:42,326
When you won the game, why did you

760
00:37:43,027 --> 00:37:44,762
pick the option of cooking?

761
00:37:45,263 --> 00:37:47,832
Why choose something that takes effort?

762
00:37:47,898 --> 00:37:48,733
Hmm…

763
00:37:48,799 --> 00:37:51,502
I wanted to do something.
I wanted to try cooking.

764
00:37:51,569 --> 00:37:54,138
And I wanted it to be just us.

765
00:37:54,205 --> 00:37:57,174
- Just us?
- Yeah. I wanted us to eat together.

766
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:02,246
And I didn't know if I'd make it well.

767
00:38:04,215 --> 00:38:05,883
When I talk with you,

768
00:38:07,485 --> 00:38:10,755
it's a little different
from talking with the others.

769
00:38:11,622 --> 00:38:14,292
I get butterflies when I'm talking to you.

770
00:38:14,792 --> 00:38:15,993
And it's fun.

771
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:19,163
And sometimes I get a bit self-conscious.

772
00:38:21,732 --> 00:38:24,769
You know… my whole body gets warm.

773
00:38:35,713 --> 00:38:37,248
Since the day I met you…

774
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:42,186
um… my feelings…

775
00:38:44,288 --> 00:38:45,589
haven't changed.

776
00:38:46,090 --> 00:38:47,358
I like you, Taeheon.

777
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:49,527
Now…

778
00:38:54,131 --> 00:38:55,199
…I want to

779
00:38:56,334 --> 00:38:57,535
know more about you.

780
00:38:58,035 --> 00:38:59,704
And I want you to know me too.

781
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:03,941
That's how

782
00:39:04,975 --> 00:39:06,043
I feel now.

783
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:11,148
<i>What should I say?</i>

784
00:39:11,215 --> 00:39:14,785
<i>What should I say right now?</i>

785
00:39:16,053 --> 00:39:17,788
I haven't said that in a while, so…

786
00:39:18,789 --> 00:39:20,358
it kinda makes me blush.

787
00:39:25,262 --> 00:39:29,033
<i>Guess we were never meant to be real</i>

788
00:39:29,100 --> 00:39:32,703
<i>Turns out we never truly promised </i>

789
00:39:32,770 --> 00:39:33,704
What?

790
00:39:33,771 --> 00:39:36,440
<i>Was anything you said even real?</i>

791
00:39:37,341 --> 00:39:39,176
- I'm happy.
- You're happy?

792
00:39:39,243 --> 00:39:42,480
<i>In my mind</i>

793
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:45,950
<i>Please stay</i>

794
00:39:46,016 --> 00:39:50,788
<i>Don't let my life</i>

795
00:39:50,855 --> 00:39:54,658
<i>Fade</i>

796
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:58,229
I want you to know me too.

797
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:01,866
And I want to know you as well.

798
00:40:02,366 --> 00:40:03,968
- That's how I feel.
- Hmm.

799
00:40:06,303 --> 00:40:09,106
But the thing is,

800
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:13,711
during our last date, honestly…

801
00:40:14,211 --> 00:40:16,881
If I'm completely honest,

802
00:40:17,948 --> 00:40:21,352
um… I wanted to talk
about a lot of things with you.

803
00:40:21,419 --> 00:40:22,420
Mmm.

804
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:26,657
Of course, the stuff
we already talked about,

805
00:40:27,391 --> 00:40:29,026
like what we talked about was,

806
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:31,462
it was like this at first,
but now it's different.

807
00:40:32,797 --> 00:40:37,501
Well, those memories…
For me, those memories are ours, and…

808
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:40,938
fun to look back on them.

809
00:40:42,740 --> 00:40:47,178
Since I realized we didn't
really get to talk about other stuff,

810
00:40:47,244 --> 00:40:49,980
I felt a bit unsettled about it.

811
00:40:51,682 --> 00:40:53,818
When I tried to talk seriously,

812
00:40:54,318 --> 00:40:56,987
I mean, kind of… you'd dodge it a little,

813
00:40:57,054 --> 00:40:58,889
or you'd laugh it off.

814
00:40:58,956 --> 00:41:00,658
That's you, Jobu.

815
00:41:00,724 --> 00:41:02,393
I don't think…

816
00:41:03,594 --> 00:41:09,366
just being attracted to each other
means we move to the next stage.

817
00:41:09,433 --> 00:41:11,235
At least, that's how I feel.

818
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:14,805
<i>In my life</i>

819
00:41:15,306 --> 00:41:18,175
<i>Hey </i>

820
00:41:18,242 --> 00:41:22,346
<i>Stay in my mind </i>

821
00:41:23,147 --> 00:41:25,983
<i>Please stay </i>

822
00:41:26,050 --> 00:41:30,855
<i>Don't let my life </i>

823
00:41:31,355 --> 00:41:34,658
<i>Fade</i>

824
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:40,030
Oh.

825
00:41:40,097 --> 00:41:44,568
We can finally see, after all this time,
where Taeheon's head is at.

826
00:41:44,635 --> 00:41:48,072
- Jobu's just been saying the same thing.
- Exactly! That's it.

827
00:41:48,138 --> 00:41:51,575
- Things were one way, but now he's happy.
- Or, "On the first date it was like this…"

828
00:41:51,642 --> 00:41:55,446
- Maybe his conversation is too simple.
- He wanted to talk about more things.

829
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:58,082
So basically,
he felt like there was more to say, right?

830
00:41:58,148 --> 00:42:00,351
So what exactly
does he want him to talk about?

831
00:42:00,417 --> 00:42:01,952
The future.

832
00:42:02,019 --> 00:42:04,421
- Oh… his vision?
- Yes. And, um… sorry.

833
00:42:04,488 --> 00:42:06,056
- I might be overstepping--
- That's right!

834
00:42:06,123 --> 00:42:08,192
- Please, go ahead.
- Yes, that's me.

835
00:42:08,259 --> 00:42:10,594
- You remember Izaya?
- You taught us a lesson.

836
00:42:10,661 --> 00:42:12,062
We're the type who wants to hear

837
00:42:12,129 --> 00:42:14,832
just roughly what kind of life
or family someone wants to build.

838
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:17,768
Anything about the future.
Even a bit shared makes us feel reassured.

839
00:42:17,835 --> 00:42:20,337
- Ah, I see, that's it.
- Oh! Good, thanks. Sorry, sorry.

840
00:42:20,404 --> 00:42:23,073
- I'm his representative!
- Sorry, I totally forgot.

841
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,141
Yes, his advocate.

842
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:27,344
- He's into future vision talk.
- Stuff about the future, huh.

843
00:42:27,411 --> 00:42:30,414
If there's a clear topic to discuss,
of course that would be great.

844
00:42:30,981 --> 00:42:32,683
Even without a set topic, as we talk more…

845
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:33,684
Look at her go.

846
00:42:33,751 --> 00:42:35,319
…a vision of the future naturally forms.

847
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:36,954
Wait… are you a robot?
